from multiple friends for a long time.  I started a character on Morell-Thule because one of my friends played there.  I started playing around with a high elf mage.  He was around level 5 when he made the big trip to Kelethin from Felewithe.  I was grouped with my wife's character at the time.<br><br>Up on one of the flets in Kelethin, I was suddenly presented with a trade screen.  I had never seen one before.  Not sure what to do, I hit the enter key and said &quot;What are you doing&quot;.  The other person said &quot;Just click the trade button&quot;.<br><br>Well, I got a real nice helmet that increased INT, mage only.  I couldn't believe it.  Wow!<br><br>The person that gave it to me was named Hamadryad Long.  The only reason I can remember that is because I'm a big Robert Heinlein fan (sorry if that doesn't explain anything).<br><br>I said to my wife &quot;I hope I can do this someday&quot;.  Hamadryad, like she read my mind, said &quot;Pass this on someday when you're ready&quot;, or something like that.<br><br>Well, I gave up the mage a week or so later, and started a cleric one Saturday morning.  I had more fun healing other newbies than I ever had before.  Now THIS is fun!<br><br>The cleric progressed until I had Ward Undead.  Skeletons got too easy.  I'm going to Unrest!  In Unrest, I met a lot of others, one of whom I sponsored in the guild after I became a member.  Anyway, one day some friends sent me a tell that they were fighting gobs in BBM, and wanted me to get there ASAP.  I sent them an &quot;OMW&quot;, and started to leave Unrest.  On the way out, there was this wolf, so I stopped and said, &quot;I am in need of haste, can you help me?&quot;<br><br>Well, not only was I sow'ed, but got so many other buffs my buff bar almost exploded.  I /bowed, and then saw a bunch of other people with my wolf friend that all had &lt;Random Acts&gt; floating over their heads.  I don't remember the names of the players, but I remember the wolf was Hamadryad Long.  I thanked her profusely, and she said &quot;Our pleasure&quot; - I will always remember that.<br><br>Now, roll the clock forward a month or so.  I'm a big man at level 16 or so, and I'm in Butcherblock.  By this time, I had given out some weapons and armor to newbies in front of kaladim, just for the fun of watching their surprise.  I heard someone auctioning a Scarab Breastplate.  I sent him a tell that I had just given one of those away, and he would get a lot more out of watching the reaction from giving it to a newbie then whatever he could get in plat.  He replied that I sounded like one of those &quot;Random Acts&quot; people.  He made it sound almost like that was a bad thing.  Now, I had to find out what he meant.<br><br>So, I looked around and tracked down what Random Acts was.  I never made the connection to &quot;Random Acts of Kindness&quot; until I found the guild site.  I can't explain how good I felt when I found that not only were there others who enjoyed giving in Norrath, but that there was a guild dedicated to what gave me the most satisfaction in playing EQ!<br><br>Not only that, but the guild did not expect anything except my trying to spread a wonderful infection throughout Norrath.  I didn't have to prove anything.  I just could associate with the people that enjoyed the same thing I did.<br><br>Problem was, I didn't know anyone in RA.  But the web site said that was OK, so I just applied.  Wipl and Emerest both volunteered as sponsors.  I started my newbie quest and looked forward to the next FA camp.<br><br>Unfortunately, the camp was at LOIO, and I was a little nervous about going there.  Hamadryad had posted that she would be in Freeport for fledglings that were too low a level to get to LOIO.  So, on Saturday, about three hours before the camp, I came online, and saw Hamadryad was on.  I sent here a /tell saying I had never been to Kunark, I was a fledgling at level 18, and should I just go to Freeport?  She said she would come get me.  Yikes, I wasn't sure what to do, but I met her at the docks in Butcherblock.<br><br>I had the true honor of riding the shuttles and boat to FV with her, and got to talk to the lady that founded this great guild.  I found out she was indeed named after a Heinlein character, and we talked most of the way about his novels.  I then had her escort me to the windmill in LOIO, to be sure I got there safely.<br><br>At the FA camp, I finally saw all the names I had seen on the BBS, and ran around healing and buffing my head off.  The first person I helped was way low on health, and I healed and buffed the snot out of him, at least as much as I could.  He thanked me profusely.  All I could say, even though I was not tagged yet, is &quot;Our pleasure&quot;, the same as Hama once told me.  I still say that whenever someone thanks me at an FA camp.<br><br>I got tagged, my brand new guildchat exploded with welcomes, and I was so happy I honestly almost cried.<br><br>Nothing, nothing in Norrath is as good as this guild.  I got what I wanted.  Not prestige.  Not twinks.  Just a bunch of the very best people I have met in Norrath, all sharing the same joy in giving, in whatever way they can, without any need for thanks or recognition except to know they are doing what they think is the right thing.<br><br>That is why I joined Random Acts.<br><br>Gimley Stoutheart, cleric of Kaladim<br>Lodrood, druid of Rivervale <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/ubalamurstoutfaith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balamur Stoutfaith</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>RA Retired Officer<br><font color=red>The invisible dorf!</span><br>  Posts: 788<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/30/02 11:46:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1597.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why I joined Random Acts</span><hr size=1> *smiles* And that's how it should be.<br><br>My first enounter with Random Acts was as a lowly Barbarian Warrior... about my 5th character ever, of which only 2 had made it past 10th level (Kemas, my deceased Paladin, and Balamur). So there I stood, 6th level, shivering the cold outside Halas knowing I wanted to be in East Commons hunting orcs. I knew nothing about Permafrost or Everfrost or Black Burrow and I didn't want to at the time. I hated new places, they were so confusing and frightening.<br><br>So there I stood with perhaps 4 or 5 pieces of tattered armor, a sowing kit I bought myself, a bronze long sword a passing high level had practically thrown at me, and a desire to be amongst familiar surroundings.<br><br>/shout Can someone show me the way to East Commons?<br><br>I met my first Random Acts person that day... a bard. Shame on me, it's been so long I cannot remember their name. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  They not only volunteered, but ran me the whole way. Newbie fears and all (I'd never been to the Karanas, talk about big scarey places at 5th level!). We ran through North Karanas with about 20 lions chasing us, I was chanting in group say don'tstopdon'tstopdon'tstop hehe.<br><br>Flash foward many months and levels later. My 4th or 5th guild has just gotten into a huge fight about... you guessed it, loot and levels. I was so tired, tired of the games, tired of the fighting, the pettiness, the downright hate and disregard for eachother. I had had enough... I detagged myself and almost &quot;pull the trigger&quot; on the account. During those last few months I had started lurking around these very forums, posting from time to time here just to keep in touch with these great and wonderful people. At the depths of my despair, I was dragged out of it when I was readily accepted here. I finally found what I'd been looking for... friends and family. Electronic strangers, sure... but closer to me than most of my flesh and blood family had ever been in all my years.<br><br>I made friends, helped where I could, ran a lot of my own little solo FA camps (since I had such horrible luck attending the official ones), and generally tried to be helpful enough to offset my dorfish attitude. Being, at the time, amongst a very small slice of RA members in their higher levels I became very proud of the determination of those around me. I had a lot of fun learning with them, and even teaching a few (to date myself... hey Meriel, remember learning to kite? That was so fun!) a trick or two.<br><br>Random Acts is my online family, regardless of whether or not I'm playing this silly game or another one, or none at all as has been the case lately. I've said this before but nobody ever asks so it must not have been said enough yet. If anyone needs the services of a 52nd level Kaotic Dorf Kleric... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><hr align="center" width="80%" size="2"><center><table width="98%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1" border="1">  <tr><td align="center"><font size="2"><b>Balamur</b><BR><font size="1">52nd Cleric of Brell<br>Morell Thule</i></td><td align="center"><font size="2"><b>Wimbuk</b><BR><font size="1">38th Clockwork Mage<br>Morell Thule</i></td><td align="center"><font size="2"><b>Aldrec</b><BR><font size="1">32nd Northman Warrior<br> Morell Thule</i></td><td align="center"><font size="2"><b>Zickt</b><BR><font size="1">23rd Swifttail Monk<br>Morell Thule</i></td><td align="center"><font size="2"><b>Drizek</b><BR><font size="1">22nd Teir'Dal Bonecaster<br>Morell Thule</i></td><td align="center"><fo