ople, asked Amerygn to sponsor me and he did and it went from there..so here I am..a vah'shir bard*no more druid for me..tried it..got bored*, I'm happy to be in the guild and part of a family I thought I would never be part of again.<br><br>Thanks all for letting me join, for being there and tolerating me..now if only I can meet my sponsor/mentor face to face<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><br>Sangreal.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/brandomacts.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eedelia01>Eedelia01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/31/02 12:57:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1597.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why I joined Random Acts</span><hr size=1> I've been in the guild for while but not as long as some. However when my father joined I started watching Random Acts. <br>        This wasn't the first game I had seen groups of people who like to add a tag to their name and say they belong. I play many many other games, but I had never joined a &quot;guild&quot; or a &quot;clan&quot; or a &quot;tribe&quot;. The reason being was because I felt stronger and more assured of my victory when I played by myself. These groups seemed to band together for a time, then quarrls would break out, fighting, and eventually what walls they had built would crumble around them.<br>       I would ask constantly about the guild and though I was level 9 at the time I was very excited at the chance to join. Ortaak..my frist RA friend taught me in the way I should go and has aided me many times sense my initiation. <br>       My favorite past times are just droping by The Greater Faydark. Thats where the action is, many get struggled very easily there and a bind is always in demand. ^_^ I love TPing in and mowing down a bunch of orcs and then giving away armor and the like. Its a great way to promote the guild and more importantly, to show others that this is isn't a Me VS You game, this is a Us VS NPC game. I'll lend you my magic, you lend me your sword and all shall fall before us. It's only when we work together that nothing seems impossible.<br>       Random Acts is different than any other group I've encountered. We don't have power hungry leaders, we have friends that look out for our best intrest as well as the countless others of Noraath. <br>       This guild taught me that everyone is help. Level 9s to level 40s, we are all help and all have a speical gift to give to others. We're all important.  <br>       I wanted to join a guild where I could make friends, and now I have so many its nearly impossible to keep track of them all. I feel accepted and wanted here, and I hope the generations of RAers that are yet to come will feel the same warmth and joy I feel when in the presence of my guildes.<br><br>Thats why I joined Random Acts<br><br>Eedelia Runespark<br>Wizard of the 31th circle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/brandomacts.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=grimmbaldis>Grimmbaldis</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>Official Guild Grouch<br>RA Officer/<br> Council Assistant<br><font color=blue>Moderator<b></span><br>  Posts: 1174<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/31/02 5:20:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1597.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why I joined Random Acts</span><hr size=1> I came to EQ after about 16 years of beta testing and MUDing.  In all those years, I never even grouped with anyone else, much less joined a guild.  So, I finally broke down and bought EQ after AC wanted to charge me $60 to keep my test account.  I made a human warrior because I thought they would be the easiest to play and give me a chance to learn the game commands.  I ventured out to West Karanas at the tender level of 8 and hit the bandit farm.   Out there, I met this weird trio of pathetic losers - Tchallar, Uriel, and Talidas.  :-)<br><br>We stayed out there for a couple of weeks, leveling and getting filthy rich!  I saw my first PP from that camp.  All the while, I kept hearing about this really cool lady named Hamadryad who wanted to start a guild.  Talidas tried his best to talk me into helping them get it set up, but I refused.  Yes, that is right, I turned down the opportunity to be a founding member of RA!!  Feel free to gasp and throw fruit.  I resisted the attempts of my friends for another week or so to join and then one day, Hama herself came out.  <br><br>Hama asked me why I wasn't interested in joining the guild since I so obviously enjoyed the company of its members and they enjoyed mine.  I told her that I was rude, crude, and socially unacceptable.  I also did not like people.  Hama told me that I was perfect for the guild just for those qualities.  That she wanted unique people to fill the ranks of RA, all dedicated to spreading a bit of kindness throughout Norrath.  And, well, nobodys says "No" to Hama for long.  :-)   So, I became the 11th <?> member of Random Acts and part of it's first group of prospects.<br><br> <p><table width="75%" border="0" align="center"><tr> <td bgcolor="#000000"> <div align="center"><img src="http://user.netomia.com/Uriel/grimmbaldis1.jpg" width="500" height="220" border="0"></div></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000>