 START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I have made alot of friends in this guild that I know will still be my friends long after EQ is no more.<br><br>I don't play much anymore but believe me I read the boards everyday and sometime try to get on to say hi because I still think of you guys. <p>Neaoh Anklebiter<br>Druid of  46 Seasons<br>Random Acts of Morell Thule</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/ugwion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gwion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b><font color=yellow>RA Council Member</font><br><b><font color=blue>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 1441<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/31/02 9:54:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1597.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why I joined Random Acts</span><hr size=1> I started playing EQ at the urging of Aganitte.  He kept telling me how fun it was.  I kept telling him I liked cyberpunk games <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   (Still do actually!)<br><br>Ag and I played on Bertox for about a year.  I had a great time--I played a male rogue, joined an all-rogue uberguild, did all kinds of fun stuff with guild wars and fighting--but nobody ever figured out I wasn't a guy! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  They never asked, I never mentioned it.<br><br>Finally, though, I started yearning for new people and places.  On about the third day Morell-Thule was up, I took the plunge and started over.  <br><br>I worked nights back then, so there was NOBODY around anywhere--try being the only person in the Butcherblock mountains!  Boy, that was bizarre.  And when I did find someone else, they were French.  My French is terrible.  I had lots of fun trying to communicate with groups.<br><br>Eventually, I met some people who spoke English--another druid named Amatraya, a ranger named Rwyan, and my old pal Cobaaca (now Kizor/Jarinth).  They were great to hang out with.  They even helped me stay up so I could switch over to a day schedule; that was funny.  &quot;No, don't go to sleep yet!  you can do it, one more hour!&quot; etc.<br><br>I got to level 14 without leaving Faydwer.  And then, as you know if you read my &quot;Our Mission&quot; post, I met Hama and the crew.  Since then, I've been in RA.<br><br>I joined RA because I was bored of playing with people who were frantic to get to the next level and grab the next new item.  A lot of the guys in my rogue guild were really nice, but they were pretty focused on leveling, and it got dull.<br><br>I knew RA was a fit for me, because here were a bunch of people who actually LIKED helping others out.  They didn't think I was weird for going all the way to Antonica to get fire beetle eyes to give out on Faydwer.  They thought that was fun too!  <br><br>And they didn't try to urge me onward all the time.  Slow is how I play, and it can tick people off sometimes because they want me to catch up.  But being a slow leveler in RA is great -- I've grouped with just about everybody at one time or another <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br><br>And nobody ever looks sideways at me for wanting to do something that doesn't involve xp--like hanging out with a bunch of lowbies for hours and hours, or dragging people all over Norrath with teleports <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I can always find someone to hang out with me, too.  And nobody makes fun of me for it--well, most of the time <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Everquest, like real life, is often boring and sometimes exasperating.  The thing that makes it bearable is having people who will listen to you, help you out with questions, and sometimes just loaf around doing nothing with you.<br><br>That's you guys.  Thanks for being in our guild, everybody.<br><br> <p><font color=green><font size=3>Gwion Llewellyn</font><br><font color=white><font size=2>Level, um, 43<br>"The flapping...the endless flapping..."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/ukaral2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karal2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b><font color=yellow>Officer<br>Retired Council Member </font><br><b><font color=blue>Administrator<br>Website Coordinator<br><font color=red>Ethical Medal of Action</font></span><br>  Posts: 758<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/31/02 11:04:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1597.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why I joined Random Acts</span><hr size=1> Well, I got into EQ because a guy at work told me about it, and I had been into D &amp;D from way back when it first came out (just the first 3 manuals at that time), and this guy told me that EQ was just like D &amp; D. But of course he was fairly high level so I knew I would never get to join him.<br><br>  He suggested that I start out with a warrior so as not to have to learn too much to start with. And he suggested the MT server as it had just come up in the last month. So Karal was born in Freeport.<br><br>   Now then, I am a fairly slow typer, so I didnt really talk to folks too much, and was really just learning the game. I had not really made any EQ freinds and alot of the folks that I did interact with just werent that freindly or helpful with such a newbie. I was actually on the verge of quitting as my free month was close to expiring. Then one day, as I hunted alone in EC (I had never even been further then EC, except for one deadly visit to WC), when I saw an /ooc. &quot;New guild being formed, based on kindness and helping others&quot; Well, turns out Hama was seeking some others to form RA, and this idea appealed to me, since it would be nice to actually find some nice folks to play with. After a few tries, I was able to send her a tell, and she came to talk to me for a minute.<br><br>   Next thing I knew we were camping out to a chat room (she told me about the rooms). There I meet a few other folks, and we talked while waiting to get ten folks together at one time in the room to approve the formation of the guild. We finally managed to get our ten folks and boom RA was formed. Well approved at least. In those days itt could take a week or so to get a GM to actually tag a guildleader. And a few days after Hama got her tag, we managed to get together and I got my tag. For me the rest is history.<br><br>    I am so happy that I replied to that /ooc, as I really would have quit, and never have had the chance to spend time with all the many wonderful folks that have worn the tag over the what 18 or so months that RA has been around. It has trully been an honor and priveledge to be associated with all you folks. <p><img src="http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze2rj22/images/gsign1.jpg" ></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/uravenmystpeaceheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravenmyst Peaceheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/1/02 12:52:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1597.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Why I joined Random Acts</span><hr size=1> Jellybean here. Gimley, thanks for starting this thread, I believe all of us should respond to this post and one that should be bumped when you feel its fading out.<br><br>    Ah the memories of old!  I first started my EQ playing days on Rallos Zek back in April of ‘99.  It was a rough environment.  Within the first 20 minutes of my EQ life I was pked and my starting sword was then looted away.  It was that very second, I knew I wanted to fight for the good and make the gaming world of this game I’ve been waiting for years to come true (many different races and classes in graphics and not through a text-mud).  A couple of other folks felt the same and thus &quot;Hand of Norrath&quot; was formed.  We started from scratch, the highest member was a level 13 warrior. We knew it would be tough for a bunch of shamans and warriors to fight off the pure casters such as wizzies, but didn’t matter, because we had the love, trust, and care for each other to help us through.  As months grew, we grew as the guild known on the server as the strong anti-pkers guild on the server.  Risking our lives to safe those who were in need of help from these pkers.  We were also known as the guild who would buff up all the newbies so they can live and simply make their EQ lives fun and enjoyable.  None of us cared about being being the highest level people out there (then again, seeing someone in full bronze in your 20’s was a haw-dropping experience). We pretty much were the Random Acts of Rallos Zek and well to be honest, that says a lot for a guild on RZ. <br>  <br>     I then decided to quit EQ to settle RL things.   After three months, my life was back on track and went back to EQ, but this time I was in the process of looking for a blue server, simply because I didn’t want to deal with the stress of being ganked on RZ.  Back then I was a frequent reader on the stratics board and decided to check out the &quot;guilds&quot; section. Lone and behold, I saw a post by Lady Hamadryad.  The post was pretty much how she was starting a new guild on one of the servers that just came live.  Of course, the part of the post about practicing kindness immediately interested me because it sounded like my old guild.  I directly went to the site and simply fell in love with it. The touching words of Lady Hamadryad and her belief of helping others through kindness and my only other experience from Hand of Norrath did me in.I went to the board and posted that I wanted to join. Ya guys remember the forum layout back then, just a tad different now isn’t it? Hehe.  Well, like Gorte, I remember that night very well.  In that chat room, I remember Lady Hamadryad had to get her son to help out  and recruit people in the general chat to get enough people to start up the guild.  It was nerve racking that night trying to get at least 10 people to stay and remain in the chat room to send in the approval.  It was like de je vu all over again. A guild starting from scratch with basically the same ideals.  A dream come true for me.  Not only will it be like my old guild but on a blue server as well, where I can relax and have fun.<br><br>   Well, after a week or so if I remember correctly, the guild was approved and I received a tell from Lady Hamadryad to hear the great news. My very first time I saw a Random Act tag was when I did a /who all on Lady Hamadryad after that tell. You would be lucky to even see more then 4 RA’s on doing a /who all. Also, none would be over level 20 except Ealwen, a high elf cleric who just seemed to sky rocket through levels, our first &quot;uber&quot; character.  Okay, kunark wasn’t out and if you were lvl 40 + you were uber to me..lol.  If you did /w who all, it was like everyone was so far apart.  Luckily for me, I already brought Jelly from Gnome town to his hang out place. That day, a gnome enchanter still wearing his banana yellow suit robe got tagged into the guild. I still remember the time of day it was in Norrath, it was during a sunset right in the spot where the loathsome individuals hung around in front of the Blackburrow entrance.  Don’t remember the exact number I was to get into the guild like Gorte and Grim does, I’m pretty sure I was one of the first ten. But that day, I knew something special happened and it still lives on to this day: Random Acts of Kindness.  A guild that was born and made up of people coming from past servers and new to everquest in general with one common goal.  The goal of making everquest a place where we can share kindness to everyone, not just for their lives in everquest, but life in general.  That itself is a gift that will live on in everyones mind and heart forever, even when there is no longer a Random Acts.  Thank you and take care all.<br><br>Jellybean Goodheart<br>Proud member of Random Acts<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/uaganitte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aganitte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>RA Member</span><br>  Posts: 229<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/1/02 1:56:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1597.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/15/1791915.jpg?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flez