tself, its very design.<br><br>But, seeing that Gwion was having a good time on MT, I reluctantly joined her on our server, starting a druid, Aganitte. At first, it was honestly just for kicks. A druid, not too dependent on items or cash, could goof around, and perhaps, this time, enjoy the game without stepping onto the manic treadmill of loot and levels.<br><br>The first thing that struck me when I met Gwion's friends is that they seemed 'real'. Wether it was just a change in my attitude, or just the nature of of these folks, these people started to -matter-. Previously, with one or two exceptions, the people on my old server were 'vehicles' for grouping and leveling and basically, continuing on the treadmill. Like some junkie in rehab, my life in MT eased me off the desire for 'material' possessions (they're pixels, c'mon). When I logged onto EQ, I found myself thinking "I wonder what Cobacca's up to" instead of "I hope Cobacca's on so we can get xp at the Bandit camp".<br><br>There's a line in a Husker Du song that says "If you don't stop to smell the roses, they might end up on you". My rebirth on MT was very much me stoping to smell the roses and I was very much in peril of ending my EQ life embittered, hitting that cancel button on the Bertoxx account.<br><br>Weeks went by, and Gwion joined Random Acts. Now, you've probably noticed it by now, but Gwion and I, although together in RL, stay pretty separate in EQ. I hung out with her, and met her friends, but I was rather reluctant to join RA. <br><br>I'm not one for groups of people. I feel left out, half the time, and the point of large groups often seems simply to 'gang up', just like Eedelia mentioned earlier. I also knew that groups were prone to infighting, greed, power mongering. I'm a skeptical person by nature, and it took me a good month or two to join RA, even after hanging out with guildmembers for ages and ages.<br><br>It took one FA camp to turn me around, and hunger to be part of this guild. <br><br>And now, I'm content here. The people I know I have high respect for, and I will be in this guild in its best times, and in its worst times. Folks often mourn the good ole days, the fear that the RA spirit may be lost. I've been with the guild long enough to know its all cycles, ever evolving cycles. Our troubles today seem large and sometimes insurmountable, but so did the ones of yesteryear.<br><br>Just remember the next time you see that Uber Dude running off with his horse, or his full Velious Armor, and you have this nagging longing to 'be uber'...ask yourself how many kind hearts does he know in EQ? More than you? <br><br> <p><CENTER><br><a href="http://www.theonion.com" target="_blank"> <img src="http://engels.freewebspace.com/images/Aga5041.gif" border="0"><br> <img src="http://engels.freewebspace.com/images/tinnasmallfixed.gif" border="0"> </a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/umorgania.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morgania</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>RA Member</span><br>  Posts: 373<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/1/02 3:12:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1597.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Why I joined Random Acts</span><hr size=1> Well, it seems very fitting for me to follow Aganitte's post as meeting her in Kelethin was the only reason I didnt quit EQ for EVER!  My bf started playing and got hooked fast and kept at me to play too, so I started a little halfelf druid, Morgania, who had a habit of falling from platforms in Kelethin <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ...being a