 1, 2001 I finally decided to play this EQ game.  I picked MT because it called out to me.  Tellia was my first and only character for a long time (20 lvls).  Tellia was born in Kelethin and the first thing I remember is OMG this is high up.  I didn't know how to get down.  I didn't know how to get down.<br><br>Finally I learned some things after trial and error.  I went thru lvls 1 - 5 in one day if I remember correctly.  I stop playing for about 36 hours.  I came back and there was all this people gathered around the POD lift.  I never saw some many character in one place.  I had to take a look.<br><br>That is when I met RA.  I got buffed from everyone all at once I didn't know what to say.  I didn't know people could buff.  I was still a very noob.  The first person I got to know was Varigon.  I remember all the FS plate he had.  I think the was sitting on one of the barrels.  After he got off it, I proceeded to try.  It looked fun.  He tried for 5 minutes to show me how to jump.<br><br>Well if you find Varigon <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  you find Meriel.  I met her that day too.  I mostly talked to Varigon that day thou.  I asked so many questions, I am surprised he still talks to me.  I asked him how do I go about getting a sponsor.  Then he said to do the /who all random.  Then I asked him if he could be my sponsor.  He said yes....<br><br>Well this was the days when Varigon played his alts more, he said that he knew what I was doing all the time.  And he did.  After I went to the RA camp and 2 lvls later, I met Toggler.  Toggler and I hit if right off, and we never be seperated since.<br><br>When toggler wasn't on and I was bored, I wanted to help everyone I saw.  Being a bard made that hard.  I couldn't buff anyone, and all my healings took to long.  So I decided to do /ooc If anyone needs help finding your body please send tells.  All for free no charge.  Being in Kelethin <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  you know i was never bored again.<br><br>I remember back then, you had to wait until the beginning of the next month to be tagged.  I didn't sleep at all.  I was looking for any officer, so they can tag me at 12:00:01 on Feb 1, 2001.  I had to wait <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Hama tagged me at 4:20am... so I didn't have to wait to long.  <br><br>Varigon didn't warn me that my chat bar would never be the same again until after I joined.  Once I was in RA I knew it was where I belonged.  Everyone was always so nice.  Finrael, Varigon, and Meriel took me to Felwithe to see the top of the world... I didn't see it that day, but they took like 2 hours just trying to teach me.<br><br>I joined RA because we don't fight to see who can loot things <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  we fight to give things away.  That is why I am here.<br><br>Tellia <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/uelryyc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elryyc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>RA Member</span><br>  Posts: 191<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/3/02 10:43:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1597.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why I joined Random Acts</span><hr size=1> I have been enjoying reading these stories... especially when I saw my son's post here and realized he joined with you partly by my involvement, but also after determining what HE wanted. It's nice to know he has a mind of his own, and isn't just my mind-slave... MUUUHHAHAHHAHAHAHHA !<br><br>Why I joined RA - well, which time ? The first time I joined RA, I had just begun playing with a shaman character on my son's account. (Which is why EED is a lvl 30-something and I'm not ! :D ) I was in Halas as a lvl 9 shaman, and I saw this guy named Hezrhond with a really COOL bent staff thingy, but dressed similar to me with a wolf helmet. I said something about, hey, cool staff, and he said thanks. We talked for a little bit, and somehow things got around to quests. Well, the next thing ya know, Hez & I are standing in the Shaman's guild and he's coaching me on what to say and who to say it to. WHen I found out I had to go THROUGH Blackburrow and on to QEYNOS !!!, I said, "well, hey, thanks but, I'm not ready for that !" And he said, "oh no worries, I'll go every step of the way with you." And I think I said something like "????, Why in the world would you do that ? You don't even KNOW me ! And I can't pay you, I'm saving for my lvl 9 spells still." Hezrhond just laughed, and I think he boggled too, "Why, Man, Have ye never heard of the Guild, Random Acts ?" Then he proceeded to buy the rest of my lvl 9 spells for me !<br><br>Well, no, I hadn't ! I had just started playing, and I didn't really trust anyone. Espescially those snotty guild-tagged people who sneered at us new people and called us dumb N00BS. SO he proceeded to tell me a few things, which sounded so awesome. I mean these guys played the game the way I liked to play, helping people, healing, buffing, guiding... things I did even as a level 1. (The time I tried to help a person get there corpse from BB and I was just a lvl 8 is a funny if tragic sidebar to my career, hehe).<br><br>So, here we are standing in the bank in Halas. Hez was about to lead me to adventure, when someone sent a shout,"Can anyone heal me at the docks?" I ooc'd back - "Sure just a sec..." and "Excuse me Hezrhond - I gotta do something then we can go..." and ran to the dock where I buffed, healed and performed my first ever SOW. I would have been there sooner, if I had SoWed my self first, heheh.<br><br>"Used up all my mana, sorry... let me regenerate and I'll be ready to go. Tell me more about Random Acts... it sounds like fun. Hope I can be worthy to get in a guild like that someday !" Hezrhond smiled at me and then said the fateful words, "Hmmmm.... maybe you will!"<br><br>Well - the rest of the story - ran through the tunnels, fell into the pool at BB and almost got wasted by Gnolls, learned when NOT to use Follow, made it through the tunnel to Qeynos, remembering being terrified, and awestruck, at the new world I found myself in. and Hezrhond repeatedly reassuring me everything was fine, not mocking me, and leading me through every step of the way to the bank guard in Qeynos for the poster, gating back, giving it to the guy at the shaman guild and BOOM!! I have a new amulet that gives me a magic hammer !!! WOW !!!! What a rush - my first quest !<br><br>I had one friend at the time - her name was Wani and her husband was in Tyrn S'Gnath, or whatever it is. They wanted me to join them, and I was all set until that fateful day with Hezrhond.... I kept stalling until I made her a little mad at me and they started PLing like mad to get her up to the acceptable level. <br><br>I applied for membership and was accepted about a week after that meeting with Hezrhond. When Wani saw my tag, which I was VERY proud of, she said, we'll you've made your decision, congratulations !! I never saw her again! :(<br><br>I was a whirlwind of emotion in those days. Sometimes I would get so aggravated I would think about quitting altogether, and you, my family, would reassure me it was going to be ok. Especially this cutie Lilone, a lil gnomey chick who was so convinced the guildremove command was broken, I tried to help her out by sending the command in a tell. Forgot the /R and ended up detagging accidently. MAN THAT WAS SCARY !!! But funny too, noe, eh, Whissers ???<br><br>I loved being in RA - but I was bored and frustrated with ELryyc, stuck at 18. Tried some new characters - none were right.... Finally decided I just wasn't having any fun, especially after my hunting pal, Silvertip left to play AC. Gave up all my worldly possessions, said goodbye and deleted Elryyc and all my alts. End of Story<br><br>Well.... not exactly.... 3 months later, lvl 30 battle-caster Li' Mui' Bai gets a tell from his friend, the former Silvertip, that he is through with AC and moving on to DAOC. Got to thinking about my old RA friends and checking out the board and.... Well, DANG IT !!! Yer my family, and I missed you ! So here I am again !<br><br>Why I joined RA the second time around ??? FAMILY, LOVE. HONOR, RESPECT !! No other motives... I want to BE RA.<br><br>Sorry such a long post.<br><br> <p>"E"- Elryyc Barbarian Shaman of the 16th Rank <BR>     Elreich Warrior Dwarf of the 14th Rank<BR>Favorite saying: "But... what would you DO with a brain if you had one?"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/uwhissers.showPublicProfile?language=EN>whissers</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>RA Member</span><br>  Posts: 164<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/3/02 5:17:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1597.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why I joined Random Acts</span><hr size=1> El, I will never forget you trying to help me with that /guildremove. That is the first time I had actually ever talked to you. I was trying to help someone with their guildremove, and had no idea how to do it. So you detagged yourself trying to tell me how. I felt awful for you and tried to tell you I was sorry, but all